text: This is interesting...if an effect allows you to cast a spell without paying the mana cost you get to choose whether to cast the spell as an Adventure. The really interesting part is, the player who controls that spell as it resolves is the one who can cast it from exile as a creature later.
So if you cast someone else's Adventure card (e.g. an Etali trigger), that same player can cast it from exile later. You need to be able to pay the appropriate mana costs, of course.

Playing my kykar tokens deck, spent half my time digging to answer the tasigur player looping evacuation and rift, I have 4 pieces of removal, 2 counters and some card draw and the guy playing unsleeved comments to me “there’s always that one control deck that won’t let people play” referring to me. What did you say?

Tbf, if he was a newbie, that table in general seems very unwelcoming. But maybe I'm projecting there.
Loopinf Rift or Evactuation certainly isn't welcoming, but I can't imagine being more mad at the person stopping it no matter how new I was
